definitions.definition: A crosspiece forming a step of a ladder; a round.
A crosspiece between legs of a chair.

definitions.example: the lowest rung of the society

definitions.definition: A floor timber in a ship.
One of the stakes of a cart; a spar; a heavy staff.
One of the radial handles projecting from the rim of a steering wheel.
One of the pins or trundles of a lantern wheel.
Of a bell, etc., to produce a resonant sound.
definitions.example: The bells were ringing in the town.

definitions.definition: To make (a bell, etc.) produce a resonant sound.
definitions.example: The deliveryman rang the doorbell to drop off a parcel.
They rang a Christmas carol on their handbells.

definitions.definition: To produce the sound of a bell or a similar sound.
Of something spoken or written, to appear to be, to seem, to sound.

definitions.example: I will ring you when we arrive.

definitions.definition: To repeat often, loudly, or earnestly.
Of a pig: having a ring through the nose.
